# .NET services

- Target .NET 8; one deployable API per folder under `services/`.
- Expose `GET /health` for orchestration and smoke tests.
- Use Serilog with correlation ID middleware (when BuildingBlocks exists).
- Database: SQL Server; dedicated database + connection string per service (`identity_db`, `catalog_db`, …). Use EF Core with `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer`.
- Publish domain events to RabbitMQ; document exchange/queue names in service README when added.

Gateway routing (Ocelot, later): `/api/{service}/...` → downstream host.
